be.v.x.0.definition: have the quality of being in the process of doing something (progressive auxiliary verb)

be.v.x.1.definition: have the quality of having something be done to one (passive auxiliary verb)

have.v.x.0.definition: have the quality of having done something (perfect aspect auxiliary verb)

will.v.x.0.definition: have the quality of being expected to do something in the future

will.v.x.1.definition: have the quality of habitually doing or having the tendency to do something

will.v.x.2.definition: have the quality of having the intention to do something

can.v.x.1.definition: have the quality of being permitted or allowed to do something

could.v.x.0.definition: have the quality of being possible for something to happen

must.v.x.1.definition: have the quality of being likely for something to happen

other.n.x.1.definition: one considered by members of a dominant group as alien, exotic, threatening, or inferior (as because of different racial, sexual, or cultural characteristics)
examples: Prejudice comes from fear of the other

other.n.x.2.definition: someone that is psychologically differentiated from the self
examples: You should have empathy for others

other.v.x.0.definition: to treat or consider (a person or a group of people) as alien to oneself or one's group
examples: we trace how in small rural communities these processes of othering the poor are racialized

we.n.x.0.definition: referring to oneself and others engaging in a common activity

we.n.x.2.definition: referring to a people in general
